parate from park fees)\",\n596:          \"category\": \"tips\",\n597:          \"amount\": 3,\n598:          \"currency\": \"USD\"\n599:        }\n600:      ],\n601:      \"legs\": [\n602:        {\n603:          \"id\": \"d47e2ad2-8d69-4dc8-a73f-e41159eeb3b4\",\n604:          \"leg\": \"Cairo (arrival stopover)\",\n605:          \"dates\": \"Aug 3-5\",\n606:          \"nights\": 2,\n607:          \"lodging\": \"Eileen Hotel\",\n608:          \"cost_usd\": 102\n609:        },\n610:        {\n611:          \"id\": \"d575efa7-6f31-4568-acdf-7582bf4ac6a4\",\n612:          \"leg\": \"Arusha (pre-safari)\",\n613:          \"dates\": \"Aug 5-7\",\n614:          \"nights\": 2,\n615:          \"lodging\": \"Serengeti Villa\",\n616:          \"cost_usd\": 62\n617:        },\n618:        {\n619:          \"id\": \"72ffef27-f2d6-4331-90b7-3b4bd227e8ee\",\n620:          \"leg\": \"Safari circuit - Tarangire / Lake Manyara / Ngorongoro Crater\",\n621:          \"dates\": \"Aug 7-9\",\n622:          \"nights\": 2,\n623:          \"lodging\": \"Suricata Safaris (Twiga camps + Jevas Hotel, package)\",\n624:          \"cost_usd\": 1200\n625:        },\n626:        {\n627:          \"id\": \"bec889d9-ada4-4984-a742-0d727cc32d92\",\n628:          \"leg\": \"Arusha (post-safari)\",\n629:          \"dates\": \"Aug 9-11\",\n630:          \"nights\": 2,\n631:          \"lodging\": \"Kutoka Lodge\",\n632:          \"cost_usd\": 96\n633:        },\n634:        {\n635:          \"id\": \"13292424-7f1c-4cde-9457-2bc59ff2b8a5\",\n636:          \"leg\": \"Zanzibar - Stone Town\",\n637:          \"dates\": \"Aug 11-13\",\n638:          \"nights\": 2,\n639:          \"lodging\": \"Treasures of Zanzibar House\",\n640:          \"cost_usd\": 100\n641:        },\n642:        {\n643:          \"id\": \"48e7050e-d66d-461c-bde9-fec2de7c0381\",\n644:          \"leg\": \"Zanzibar - beach (Kiwengwa)\",\n645:          \"dates\": \"Aug 13-17\",\n646:          \"nights\": 4,\n647:          \"lodging\": \"Ayla Beach House\",\n648:          \"cost_usd\": 304\n649:        },\n650:        {\n651:          \"id\": \"6781f37a-027f-41e1-826b-b02c8cb1315a\",\n652:          \"leg\": \"Dar es Salaam\",\n653:          \"dates\": \"Aug 17-19\",\n654:          \"nights\": 2,\n655:          \"lodging\": \"Sunny Shore B&B\",\n656:          \"cost_usd\": 200\n657:        },\n658:        {\n659:          \"id\": \"610b71d1-89a8-49ed-9aa9-0e8e03351bc2\",\n660:          \"leg\": \"Cairo (departure stopover)\",\n661:          \"dates\": \"Aug 19-20\",\n662:          \"nights\": 1,\n663:          \"lodging\": \"Ramses Hilton\",\n664:          \"cost_usd\": 87\n665:        }\n666:      ],\n667:      \"notes\": [\n668:        {\n669:          \"id\": \"e63ee840-8b81-4284-97bb-3a59c0e15997\",\n670:          \"section\": \"Purpose & Context\",\n671:          \"content\": \"Vasilis is planning a fully booked international trip in August 2026, traveling with a companion named Athina Mari. The trip spans Cairo (Egypt), Arusha and the northern Tanzania safari circuit, Zanzibar, and Dar es Salaam, running August 3–20. The trip combines cultural sightseeing in Cairo, a group camping safari through Tarangire, Lake Manyara, and Ngorongoro Crater, beach time in Zanzibar, and city exploration in Dar es Salaam. All flights, accommodations, the safari, and key dining are confirmed and fully organized. Vasilis communicates with Claude in both Greek and English interchangeably; Claude should respond in whichever language Vasilis uses.\",\n672:          \"order\": 1\n673:        },\n674:        {\n675:          \"id\": \"8135d218-a054-4ef3-bdc1-5cd8f5907487\",\n676:          \"section\": \"Current State\",\n677:          \"content\": \"All trip logistics are confirmed. No unbooked gaps remain.\",\n678:          \"order\": 2\n679:        },\n680:        {\n681:          \"id\": \"b7a2a4f9-2af3-4865-916d-182ee6c4120e\",\n682:          \"section\": \"Safari\",\n683:          \"content\": \"Suricata Safaris Ltd, 3-day group camping safari, Aug 7–9. Contact: Richard, +255 763 222 293, info@suricatasafaris.com. Cost: $1,200 total; $240 deposit paid (20%); $960 balance due on arrival in cash (USD, post-2009 notes) or online via Pesapal (+5% surcharge): payments.pesapal.com/suricatasafaris.\",\n684:          \"order\": 3\n685:        },\n686:        {\n687:          \"id\": \"78a62588-85ef-423c-8876-ec4101d84b80\",\n688:          \"section\": \"Dining\",\n689:          \"content\": \"The Rock Restaurant, Zanzibar — Aug 15, 18:00–20:00 sitting, 2 adults, 2x Tropical Passion Fruit Cheesecake included. Fully paid ($46). Outdoor seating requested for sunset/star views. Contact: +255 776 591 360 / +255 763 070 658, booking@therockrestaurantzanzibar.com.\",\n690:          \"order\": 4\n691:        },\n692:        {\n693:          \"id\": \"4bf34b9c-948b-4777-952a-3bd53add1f3c\",\n694:          \"section\": \"Driving in Zanzibar\",\n695:          \"content\": \"Vasilis holds an International Driving Permit (IDP). A local Zanzibar Driving Permit is also required (~$15, valid up to 3 months). Most rental companies arrange this with a license photo provided 24+ hours before arrival. Police checkpoints are frequent; carry both IDP and local permit (screenshot acceptable).\",\n696:          \"order\": 5\n697:        },\n698:        {\n699:          \"id\": \"c72486d1-713f-4552-852a-1f45bb55526e\",\n700:          \"section\": \"On the Horizon\",\n701:          \"content\": \"Safari balance ($960 USD, post-2009 notes) to be paid on arrival — cash preferred; Pesapal online adds 5%.\\nCairo Stopover 1 sightseeing plan: Grand Egyptian Museum and Pyramids of Giza (Aug 3–4). Eileen Hotel is near Tahrir Square/Nile Corniche.\\nCairo Stopover 2 sightseeing plan: Islamic Cairo, the Citadel, Khan el-Khalili bazaar, Coptic Cairo (Aug 19–20). Ramses Hilton is the base; taxi needed between Citadel and Coptic Cairo.\\nZanzibar activities and local exploration, including The Rock Restaurant dinner on Aug 15.\\nDar es Salaam: arriving by ferry from Zanzibar; interest in city exploration (Kivukoni Fish Market, Kariakoo Market, National Museum, Coco Beach, Bongoyo Island).\",\n702:          \"order\": 6\n703:        },\n704:        {\n705:          \"id\": \"a94a05c0-428f-420b-b5d5-96187b3e2777\",\n706:          \"section\": \"Key Learnings & Principles\",\n707:          \"content\": \"EgyptAir operates the Cairo↔Dar es Salaam legs — confirmed by Vasilis; do not second-guess this.\\nTanzania e-visa is mandatory online ($50/person) at visa.immigration.go.tz; visa-on-arrival no longer available as of January 2025. Zanzibar also requires separate mandatory travel insurance from the Zanzibar Insurance Corporation.\\nEgypt e-visa is multiple-entry ($65); both travelers apply separately. Egyptian e-visa requires a mandatory printed copy.\\nNgorongoro nights are cold — warm layers needed.\\nFor Zanzibar swimming: north coast (Nungwi area) offers more consistent conditions vs. east/south coasts where low tide limits access.\\nPrecision Air flights (TC144/TC145) have luggage restrictions favoring soft bag","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false,"persistedOutputPath":"/home/vasilis/.claude/projects/-home-vasilis-LMTHING-lmthing/f5b3cae8-3c1f-4979-9ef4-d80e7e56a620/tool-results/b22yaj60n.txt","persistedOutputSize":39633}}
