alloon landing fees vary by size.\",\n1129\t          \"sort_order\": 19\n1130\t        }\n1131\t      ],\n1132\t      \"photos\": [\n1133\t        {\n1134\t          \"id\": \"photo-1\",\n1135\t          \"title\": \"Stone Town Courtyard\",\n1136\t          \"description\": \"A bright courtyard in Stone Town, Zanzibar — tall white building with arched windows, dark wooden balconies, carved railings. Classic Zanzibari architecture.\",\n1137\t          \"location\": \"Stone Town, Zanzibar\",\n1138\t          \"date_taken\": \"Aug 2026\",\n1139\t          \"sort_order\": 1\n1140\t        },\n1141\t        {\n1142\t          \"id\": \"photo-2\",\n1143\t          \"title\": \"Ngorongoro Crater — one of the best days\",\n1144\t          \"description\": \"The Ngorongoro crater day was \\\"one of the best days\\\" of the trip. Driver-guide Emmanuel led the descent. Bought 2 beaded bracelets from a Maasai lady for ~$20-25 USD (~35,000 TZS).\",\n1145\t          \"location\": \"Ngorongoro Crater, Tanzania\",\n1146\t          \"date_taken\": \"Aug 9, 2026\",\n1147\t          \"sort_order\": 2\n1148\t        },\n1149\t        {\n1150\t          \"id\": \"photo-3\",\n1151\t          \"title\": \"The Rock Restaurant\",\n1152\t          \"description\": \"The Rock Restaurant, Zanzibar — Aug 15 dinner at 18:00. Outdoor seating for sunset and star views over the Indian Ocean.\",\n1153\t          \"location\": \"Michamvi Pingwe, Zanzibar\",\n1154\t          \"date_taken\": \"Aug 15, 2026\",\n1155\t          \"sort_order\": 3\n1156\t        },\n1157\t        {\n1158\t          \"id\": \"photo-4\",\n1159\t          \"title\": \"Tarangire National Park\",\n1160\t          \"description\": \"Tarangire — famous for its elephant herds and baobab trees. First day of the safari circuit.\",\n1161\t          \"location\": \"Tarangire NP, Tanzania\",\n1162\t          \"date_taken\": \"Aug 7, 2026\",\n1163\t          \"sort_order\": 4\n1164\t        },\n1165\t        {\n1166\t          \"id\": \"photo-5\",\n1167\t          \"title\": \"Lake Manyara\",\n1168\t          \"description\": \"Lake Manyara National Park — known for tree-climbing lions and flamingos. Second day of safari.\",\n1169\t          \"location\": \"Lake Manyara NP, Tanzania\",\n1170\t          \"date_taken\": \"Aug 8, 2026\",\n1171\t          \"sort_order\": 5\n1172\t        }\n1173\t      ],\n1174\t      \"questions\": [\n1175\t        {\n1176\t          \"id\": \"q-1\",\n1177\t          \"question\": \"Extra ranger tip at Ngorongoro gate — ~5,000 TZS cash?\",\n1178\t          \"context\": \"Emmanuel mentioned an extra ranger tip of ~5,000 TZS cash at the gate, separate from park fees. Ask Richard at Suricata Safaris before settling the safari balance.\",\n1179\t          \"status\": \"open\",\n1180\t          \"priority\": \"high\",\n1181\t          \"sort_order\": 1\n1182\t        },\n1183\t        {\n1184\t          \"id\": \"q-2\",\n1185\t          \"question\": \"Safari balance payment method — cash or Pesapal?\",\n1186\t          \"context\": \"$960 balance due on arrival. Cash (post-2009 USD notes) preferred; Pesapal online adds 5% surcharge. Confirm with Richard.\",\n1187\t          \"status\": \"open\",\n1188\t          \"priority\": \"high\",\n1189\t          \"sort_order\": 2\n1190\t        },\n1191\t        {\n1192\t          \"id\": \"q-3\",\n1193\t          \"question\": \"Zanzibar local driving permit — arrange in advance?\",\n1194\t          \"context\": \"~$15, valid up to 3 months. Most rental companies arrange with license photo 24h before arrival. Vasilis holds IDP.\",\n1195\t          \"status\": \"open\",\n1196\t          \"priority\": \"medium\",\n1197\t          \"sort_order\": 3\n1198\t        },\n1199\t        {\n1200\t          \"id\": \"q-4\",\n1201\t          \"question\": \"Zanzibar mandatory travel insurance (ZIC) — purchase before arrival?\",\n1202\t          \"context\": \"$44/person, mandatory for Zanzibar entry. Confirm whether to buy online in advance or on arrival.\",\n1203\t          \"status\": \"open\",\n1204\t          \"priority\": \"high\",\n1205\t          \"sort_order\": 4\n1206\t        },\n1207\t        {\n1208\t          \"id\": \"q-5\",\n1209\t          \"question\": \"Tanzania e-visa application timeline\",\n1210\t          \"context\": \"$50/person at visa.immigration.go.tz. Both travelers need to apply. Visa-on-arrival no longer available.\",\n1211\t          \"status\": \"open\",\n1212\t          \"priority\": \"high\",\n1213\t          \"sort_order\": 5\n1214\t        },\n1215\t        {\n1216\t          \"id\": \"q-6\",\n1217\t          \"question\": \"Egypt e-visa — both travelers apply separately, print copies\",\n1218\t          \"context\": \"Multiple-entry, $65/person. Mandatory printed copy required. Apply before departure.\",\n1219\t          \"status\": \"open\",\n1220\t          \"priority\": \"high\",\n1221\t          \"sort_order\": 6\n1222\t        },\n1223\t        {\n1224\t          \"id\": \"q-7\",\n1225\t          \"question\": \"Dar es Salaam ferry from Zanzibar — book in advance?\",\n1226\t          \"context\": \"Traveling Zanzibar → Dar es Salaam by ferry on Aug 17. Confirm ferry schedule and booking.\",\n1227\t          \"status\": \"open\",\n1228\t          \"priority\": \"medium\",\n1229\t          \"sort_order\": 7\n1230\t        },\n1231\t        {\n1232\t          \"id\": \"q-8\",\n1233\t          \"question\": \"Ngorongoro warm layers — pack check\",\n1234\t          \"context\": \"Ngorongoro nights are cold. Confirm warm layers (fleece, jacket) are packed. Decathlon Forclaz trekking line recommended.\",\n1235\t          \"status\": \"open\",\n1236\t          \"priority\": \"medium\",\n1237\t          \"sort_order\": 8\n1238\t        },\n1239\t        {\n1240\t          \"id\": \"q-9\",\n1241\t          \"question\": \"Precision Air luggage — soft bags only?\",\n1242\t          \"context\": \"Flights TC144/TC145 have luggage restrictions favoring soft bags. Confirm b