: 35.4,\n          \"ea_tzs\": 8850,\n          \"expat_usd\": null,\n          \"notes\": \"\",\n          \"sort_order\": 14\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"nca-15\",\n          \"category\": \"Camping Fees\",\n          \"subcategory\": \"Special campsite per person\",\n          \"age_group\": \"16+ years\",\n          \"non_ea_usd\": 70.8,\n          \"ea_tzs\": null,\n          \"expat_usd\": null,\n          \"notes\": \"Must be reserved and confirmed prior to arrival.\",\n          \"sort_order\": 15\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"nca-16\",\n          \"category\": \"Walking Safari\",\n          \"subcategory\": \"Short walk (1–4 hours) — adult\",\n          \"age_group\": \"16+ years\",\n          \"non_ea_usd\": 23.6,\n          \"ea_tzs\": 11800,\n          \"expat_usd\": null,\n          \"notes\": \"Must be accompanied by NCAA armed ranger.\",\n          \"sort_order\": 16\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"nca-17\",\n          \"category\": \"Walking Safari\",\n          \"subcategory\": \"Long walk (above 4 hours) — adult\",\n          \"age_group\": \"16+ years\",\n          \"non_ea_usd\": 29.5,\n          \"ea_tzs\": 23600,\n          \"expat_usd\": null,\n          \"notes\": \"\",\n          \"sort_order\": 17\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"nca-18\",\n          \"category\": \"Olduvai Gorge\",\n          \"subcategory\": \"Olduvai Gorge / Shifting Sand / Laetoli Footprints\",\n          \"age_group\": \"16+ years\",\n          \"non_ea_usd\": 35.4,\n          \"ea_tzs\": 5900,\n          \"expat_usd\": 11.8,\n          \"notes\": \"\",\n          \"sort_order\": 18\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"nca-19\",\n          \"category\": \"Hot Air Balloon\",\n          \"subcategory\": \"Balloon safari per person\",\n          \"age_group\": \"8+ years\",\n          \"non_ea_usd\": 39.53,\n          \"ea_tzs\": 47200,\n          \"expat_usd\": null,\n          \"notes\": \"Locally registered balloon landing fees vary by size.\",\n          \"sort_order\": 19\n        }\n      ],\n      \"photos\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"photo-1\",\n          \"title\": \"Stone Town Courtyard\",\n          \"description\": \"A bright courtyard in Stone Town, Zanzibar — tall white building with arched windows, dark wooden balconies, carved railings. Classic Zanzibari architecture.\",\n          \"location\": \"Stone Town, Zanzibar\",\n          \"date_taken\": \"Aug 2026\",\n          \"sort_order\": 1\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"photo-2\",\n          \"title\": \"Ngorongoro Crater — one of the best days\",\n          \"description\": \"The Ngorongoro crater day was \\\"one of the best days\\\" of the trip. Driver-guide Emmanuel led the descent. Bought 2 beaded bracelets from a Maasai lady for ~$20-25 USD (~35,000 TZS).\",\n          \"location\": \"Ngorongoro Crater, Tanzania\",\n          \"date_taken\": \"Aug 9, 2026\",\n          \"sort_order\": 2\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"photo-3\",\n          \"title\": \"The Rock Restaurant\",\n          \"description\": \"The Rock Restaurant, Zanzibar — Aug 15 dinner at 18:00. Outdoor seating for sunset and star views over the Indian Ocean.\",\n          \"location\": \"Michamvi Pingwe, Zanzibar\",\n          \"date_taken\": \"Aug 15, 2026\",\n          \"sort_order\": 3\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"photo-4\",\n          \"title\": \"Tarangire National Park\",\n          \"description\": \"Tarangire — famous for its elephant herds and baobab trees. First day of the safari circuit.\",\n          \"location\": \"Tarangire NP, Tanzania\",\n          \"date_taken\": \"Aug 7, 2026\",\n          \"sort_order\": 4\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"photo-5\",\n          \"title\": \"Lake Manyara\",\n          \"description\": \"Lake Manyara National Park — known for tree-climbing lions and flamingos. Second day of safari.\",\n          \"location\": \"Lake Manyara NP, Tanzania\",\n          \"date_taken\": \"Aug 8, 2026\",\n          \"sort_order\": 5\n        }\n      ],\n      \"questions\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"q-1\",\n          \"question\": \"Extra ranger tip at Ngorongoro gate — ~5,000 TZS cash?\",\n          \"context\": \"Emmanuel mentioned an extra ranger tip of ~5,000 TZS cash at the gate, separate from park fees. Ask Richard at Suricata Safaris before settling the safari balance.\",\n          \"status\": \"open\",\n          \"priority\": \"high\",\n          \"sort_order\": 1\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"q-2\",\n          \"question\": \"Safari balance payment method — cash or Pesapal?\",\n          \"context\": \"$960 balance due on arrival. Cash (post-2009 USD notes) preferred; Pesapal online adds 5% surcharge. Confirm with Richard.\",\n          \"status\": \"open\",\n          \"priority\": \"high\",\n          \"sort_order\": 2\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"q-3\",\n          \"question\": \"Zanzibar local driving permit — arrange in advance?\",\n          \"context\": \"~$15, valid up to 3 months. Most rental companies arrange with license photo 24h before arrival. Vasilis holds IDP.\",\n          \"status\": \"open\",\n          \"priority\": \"medium\",\n          \"sort_order\": 3\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"q-4\",\n          \"question\": \"Zanzibar mandatory travel insurance (ZIC) — purchase before arrival?\",\n          \"context\": \"$44/person, mandatory for Zanzibar entry. Confirm whether to buy online in advance or on arrival.\",\n          \"status\": \"open\",\n          \"priority\": \"high\",\n          \"sort_order\": 4\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"q-5\",\n          \"question\": \"Tanzania e-visa application timeline\",\n          \"context\": \"$50/person at visa.immigration.go.tz. Both travelers need to apply. Visa-on-arrival no longer available.\",\n          \"status\": \"open\",\n          \"priority\": \"high\",\n          \"sort_order\": 5\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"q-6\",\n          \"question\": \"Egypt e-visa — both travelers apply separately, print copies\",\n          \"context\": \"Multiple-entry, $65/person. Mandatory printed copy required. Apply before departure.\",\n          \"status\": \"open\",\n          \"priority\": \"high\",\n          \"sort_order\": 6\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"q-7\",\n          \"question\": \"Dar es Salaam ferry from Zanzibar — book in advance?\",\n          \"context\": \"Traveling Zanzibar → Dar es Salaam by ferry on Aug 17. Confirm ferry schedule and booking.\",\n          \"status\": \"open\",\n          \"priority\": \"medium\",\n          \"sort_order\": 7\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"q-8\",\n          \"question\": \"Ngorongoro warm layers — pack check\",\n          \"context\": \"Ngorongoro nights are cold. Confirm warm layers (fleece, jacket) are packed. Decathlon Forclaz trekking line recommended.\",\n          \"status\": \"open\",\n          \"priority\": \"medium\",\n          \"sort_order\": 8\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"q-9\",\n          \"question\": \"Precision Air luggage — soft bags only?\",\n          \"context\": \"Flights TC144/TC145 have luggage restrictions favoring soft bags. Confirm baggage allowance and pack accordingly.\",\n          \"status\": \"open\",\n          \"priority\": \"low\",\n          \"sort_order\": 9\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"q-10\",\n          \"question\": \"DEET-based insect repellent — purchase before trip\",\n          \"context\": \"Essential for safari and Zanzibar. Recommended to source from Decathlon in Greece.\",\n          \"status\": \"open\",\n          \"priority\": \"medium\",\n          \"sort_order\": 10\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    \"appManifest\": {\n      \"tables\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"contacts\",\n          \"schema\": {\n            \"title\": \"Contacts\",\n            \"descri